items.title: Introsort - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
It begins with quicksort and switches to heapsort when the recursion depth 
exceeds a level based on (the logarithm of) the number of elements being sorted.

items.title: Quickselect - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
In computer science, quickselect is a selection algorithm to find the kth smallest 
element in an unordered list. It is related to the quicksort sorting algorithm.
items.htmlSnippet:

items.title: Talk:Quicksort/Archive 1 - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
Quicksort can actually be done in O(n log n) time worst case, by carefully 
choosing the pivot - the algorithm to do so is a bit complex though.
